    <title>Introduction</title>
    <para>
        The Maven repository is a central component of Maven, facilitating universal reuse of project artifacts
        including Maven plugins.
    </para>
    <para>
        A Maven repository is simply a storage space for artifacts generated from various projects
        and the Project Object Model (POM) describing how the artifacts can be built and what the artifact's
        dependencies are.
    </para>
